answer: The properties of SNe II-L and SNe IIn extend our understanding of supernovae, with SNe II-L showing evidence of late-time interaction with circumstellar material and SNe IIn having unusually dense circumstellar gas (astro-ph/0102485).
explanation: This paper provides an overview of optical observations of core-collapse supernovae, including SNe II-L and SNe IIn, and discusses their properties and interactions with circumstellar material.
evidence_quote: SNe II-L tend to show evidence of late-time interaction with circumstellar material
